WHEREAS, a leader among leaders, Mr. Harris is the former president of the Middle
Tennessee Athletic Conference and sat on the board of the National Christian Sports
Conference, and to better serve his student body, he returned to school to further develop his
administrative acumen, earning a Master of Education degree in Administration; and
WHEREAS, he is an extremely talented and compassionate educator who has worked
assiduously throughout his career in education to motivate his students, fellow teachers, and
staff to reach their full potential as scholars, professionals, and citizens; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Harris truly serves as an inspiration to his colleagues and students
alike, and his friendship and counsel are highly valued by those who are fortunate to know him;
and
WHEREAS, Hugh Harris epitomizes the dedicated educator who is wholly committed to
the highest ideals of public service and quality education for all, and he should be specially
recognized as he ends his journey in education; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby thank Hugh Harris for his twenty-one years of service as
headmaster and president of Franklin Christian Academy, commend his exceptional service to
the children of Tennessee, salute his professional expertise and personal excellence, and wish
him all the best in a fruitful retirement.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
